00303     //Converts a string in the form "seconds since 1970.fractional part of the last second"
00304     //to a human-readable format for display within the table.
00305     public String getTimestamp(String timeIn) {
00306         StringTokenizer tokTime = new StringTokenizer(timeIn, ".");
00307         String timeLeft = tokTime.nextToken();
00308         String timeRight = tokTime.nextToken();
00309         String uTS = "";
00310         String unixTime = "";
00311 
00312         timeRight = timeRight.substring(0, 8);
00313         
00314         Calendar myCal = Calendar.getInstance();
00315 
00316         myCal.set(1970, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0);
00317 
00318         DateFormat df = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-mm-dd HH:mm:ss");
00319 
00320         myCal.add(Calendar.SECOND, Integer.parseInt(timeLeft));
00321         unixTime = df.format(myCal.getTime());
00322 
00323         Timestamp unixTS = new Timestamp(0);
00324 
00325         unixTS = unixTS.valueOf(unixTime.toString());
00326         unixTS.setNanos(Integer.parseInt(timeRight));
00327         uTS = unixTS.toString();
00328         uTS = uTS.substring(11);
00329 
00330         return uTS;
00331     }

00967     //Internal function to facilitate taking a timestamp value in as 20:16:30.4567
00968     //and returning 2016304567
00969     public String parseCell(String cell) {
00970         StringTokenizer strTok = new StringTokenizer(cell, ":", true);
00971         
00972         String hour = strTok.nextToken();
00973         
00974         strTok.nextToken();
00975         String min = strTok.nextToken();
00976         
00977         strTok.nextToken();
00978         String sec = strTok.nextToken(".");
00979         
00980         strTok.nextToken();
00981         String milli = strTok.nextToken();
00982         
00983         String strCell = hour + min + sec + milli;
00984         strCell = strCell.substring(0, 10);
00985         
00986         return strCell;

01013             //to the labels (e.g. "1ms" = 1, "10ms" = 2, etc.).

01015             //the window to determine the end time and thus the window size.
01016             if (winSize == 1) {
01017                 beg.add(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 1);

01020                 beg.add(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 10);

01028             }
01029             else if (winSize == 5) {
01030                 beg.add(Calendar.MINUTE, 1);
01031             }
01032             else if (winSize == 6) {
01033                 tableVec = rowData;
01034                 selectEvent(eventState);

01042             String strMilli = String.valueOf(beg.get(Calendar.MILLISECOND));
01043             
01044             if (Integer.parseInt(strHour) < 10) {
